230.British-Foreign-Secretaries_text.pdf online]\n* Chassaigne, Phillipe, and Michael Dockrill, eds. ''Anglo-French Relations 1898\u20131998: From Fashoda to Jospin'' (2002)\n* {{cite book |ref=harv|last1=Chirol |first1=Valentine |authorlink=Valentine Chirol |title=The Empire and the century |date=1905 |publisher=John Murray |location=London |pages=728\u201359 |chapter=[[s:The Empire and the century/Our Imperial Interests in Nearer and Further Asia|Our Imperial Interests in Nearer and Further Asia]]}}\n* Clark, Christopher. ''The sleepwalkers: how Europe went to war in 1914'' (2012).\n*{{citation|last=Dahl |first=E.J. |title=Naval innovation: From coal to oil |journal=Joint Force Quarterly |issue=Winter 2000\u201301 |year=2001 |url=http://www.dtic.mil/dtic/tr/fulltext/u2/a524799.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161022194856/http://www.dtic.mil/dtic/tr/fulltext/u2/a524799.pdf |url-status=live |archivedate=22 October 2016 |pages=50\u20136|accessdate=28 November 2016 |df=dmy-all}}\n* Feis, Herbert. ''Europe the World's Banker, 1870\u20131914'' (1930) [https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.49015001116822;view=1up;seq=7 online]; mostly about London banks\n* Hale, Oron James. ''Publicity and Diplomacy: With Special Reference to England and Germany, 1890\u20131914'' (1940) [https://www.questia.com/library/1023289/publicity-and-diplomacy-with-special-reference-to online]\n* Hayes, Paul. ''Nineteenth Century'' (Modern British foreign policy) (1975).\n* Kennedy, Paul M. ''The Rise of the Anglo-German Antagonism, 1860\u20131914'' (1987) 600 pp \n* Kennedy, Paul M. ''The rise and fall of British naval mastery'' (1976) pp 149\u2013238.\n*{{citation|author-last=Kuiken |author-first=J. |title=Caught in Transition: Britain's Oil Policy in the Face of Impending Crisis, 1967\u20131973 |journal=[[Historical Social Research]] |volume=39 |issue=4 |year=2014 |pages=272\u201390 |jstor=24145537}}\n* Lowe, C.J. ''The reluctant imperialists: British foreign policy, 1878\u20