' (1967), 140 documents 1878\u20131902. (American edition 1969 vol 1 and 2 bound together).\n* Lowe, C.J. and M.L. Dockrill, eds. ''The Mirage of Power: Volume 3: The Documents British Foreign Policy, 1902\u201322.'' (1972), 191 documents.\n* [[Ivan Maisky|Maisky, Ivan.]] ''The Maisky Diaries: The Wartime Revelations of Stalin's Ambassador in London'' edited by [[Gabriel Gorodetsky]], (Yale UP, 2016); highly revealing commentary 1934\u201343; [https://www.amazon.com/dp/0300180675/ excerpts]; abridged from 3 volume Yale edition; [https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/jan/20/the-miasky-diaries-review online review]\n* Medlicott, W. N. ed. ''Documents on British Foreign Policy, 1919\u20131939'' (HMSO, 1946), primary sources\n* Temperley, Harold, and Lillian M. Penson, eds. ''Foundations of British Foreign Policy from Pitt (1792) to Salisbury (1902); Or, Documents, Old and New'' (1938), 612pp [https://www.questia.com/library/91479755/foundations-of-british-foreign-policy-from-pitt-1792 online]\n* Wiener, Joel H. ed. ''Great Britain: Foreign Policy and the Span of Empire, 1689\u20131971: A Documentary History'' (4 vol 1972) [https://www.questia.com/library/6963234/great-britain-foreign-policy-and-the-span-of-empire vol 1 online]; [https://www.questia.com/library/120074154/great-britain-foreign-policy-and-the-span-of-empire vol 2 online]; [https://www.questia.com/library/120073878/great-britain-foreign-policy-and-the-span-of-empire vol 3]; [https://www.questia.com/library/120073810/great-britain-foreign-policy-and-the-span-of-empire vol 4] 4 vol. 3400 pages\n\n==Further reading==\n{{Further|Historiography of the United Kingdom}}\n* [[Jeremy Black (historian)|Black, Jeremy]] et al.  ''The Makers of British Foreign Policy, From Pitt to Thatcher'' (Palgrave, Basingstoke and New York, 2002)\n\n{{Foreign relations of Europe}}\n{{United Kingdom topics}}\n\n[[Category:Historiography of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:History of the foreign relations of the United Kingdom| ]]\n