{"title_page": "European Coalition (Poland)", "text_new": "{{use dmy dates|date=July 2012}}\n{{short description|Liberal electoral alliance in Poland}}\n{{Infobox political party\n| name = European Coalition\n| logo = Logo-KE-podstawowe-biale-tlo.svg\n| colorcode = #0087BD\n| leader = {{\u2022}}[[Grzegorz Schetyna]]<br>{{\u2022}}[[W\u0142adys\u0142aw Kosiniak-Kamysz]]<br>{{\u2022}}[[:pl:W\u0142odzimierz Czarzasty|W\u0142odzimierz Czarzasty]]<br>{{\u2022}}[[Katarzyna Lubnauer]]<br>{{\u2022}}[[:pl:Marek Kossakowski (dziennikarz)|Marek Kossakowski]]<br>{{\u2022}}[[Ma\u0142gorzata Tracz]]\n| foundation = 1 February 2019\n| dissolved = 26 May 2019\n| ideology = [[Pro-Europeanism]]<br>[[Liberal democracy]]<br>[[Big tent]]\n| european = \n| headquarters = ul. Wiejska 12a, 00-490 [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]]\n| website = {{url|https://koalicjaeuropejska.pl}}\n| country = Poland\n| native_name = Koalicja Europejska\n| position = [[Big tent]]\n| seats1_title = [[Sejm of the Republic of Poland|Sejm]]\n| seats1 = {{composition bar|213|460|hex=#0087BD}}\n| seats2_title = [[Senate of Poland|Senate]]\n| seats2 = {{composition bar|48|100|hex=#0087BD}}\n| seats3_title = [[European Parliament]]\n| seats3 = {{composition bar|22|52|hex=#0087BD}}\n| abbreviation = KE\n| colors = {{color box|#0087BD|border=darkgray}} [[Blue]]\n}}\nThe '''European Coalition''' ({{lang-pl|Koalicja Europejska}}, KE) is a [[political alliance]] and [[electoral list]] in Poland established in 2019 by a group of former [[Prime Minister of Poland|prime ministers]] and former [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Poland)|foreign ministers]], including [[Jerzy Buzek]], [[Ewa Kopacz]], [[Grzegorz Schetyna]] and [[Rados\u0142aw Sikorski]]. They declared the will to construct \"one broad list in [[2019 European Parliament election|European Parliament election]], the aim of which would be to restore Poland's strong position in the [[European Union]]\". The Coalition is to be [[Pro-Europeanism|pro-European]] and [[Centrism|centrist]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wiadomosci.onet.pl/tylko-w-onecie/koniec-koalicji-obywatelskiej-schetyna-pokazuje-nowy-szyld/vx5e888|title=Koniec Koalicji Obywatelskiej, Schetyna pokazuje nowy szyld|date=2019-02-01|website=Onet Wiadomo\u015bci|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-04}}</ref>\n\nParties included in the coalition are the [[Democratic Left Alliance]] (since 16 February),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wiadomosci.gazeta.pl/wiadomosci/7,114884,24463976,sld-dolacza-do-koalicji-europejskiej-na-eurowybory-kandydatami.html|title=SLD do\u0142\u0105cza do Koalicji Europejskiej na eurowybory. Kandydatami m.in. Miller, Belka i Cimoszewicz|website=gazetapl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-17}}</ref> [[The Greens (Poland)|The Greens]] (since 17 February),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fakty.interia.pl/raporty/raport-ue-przed-wyborami-europejskimi/artykuly/news-zieloni-postanowili-o-dolaczeniu-do-koalicji-europejskiej,nId,2840963|title=Koalicja Europejska ro\u015bnie w si\u0142\u0119. Przyst\u0105pi\u0142a kolejna partia|website=fakty.interia.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-17}}</ref> [[Now! (political party)|Now!]] (since 18 February),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wyborcza.pl/7,75398,24469339,partia-teraz-dolacza-do-koalicji-europejskiej.html|title=Partia Teraz! do\u0142\u0105cza do Koalicji Europejskiej|website=wyborcza.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-18}}</ref> [[Civic Platform]] (since 21 February),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fakty.interia.pl/raporty/raport-ue-przed-wyborami-europejskimi/artykuly/news-zarzad-po-poparl-sfinalizowanie-koalicji-europejskiej,nId,2847871|title=Zarz\u0105d PO zadecydowa\u0142 w sprawie koalicji|website=fakty.interia.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref> [[.Modern|Modern]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://natemat.pl/264793,niedoficjalnie-nowoczesna-wchodzi-do-koalicji-europejskiej|title=Koalicja Europejska coraz wi\u0119ksza. Kolejna partia na wsp\u00f3lnych listach opozycji do europarlamentu|website=naTemat.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref> [[Alliance of Democrats (Poland)|Democratic Party]] (since 22 February),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dorzeczy.pl/kraj/94434/Partia-Pawla-Piskorskiego-zasili-Koalicje-Europejska-Jest-wniosek-o-akces.html|title=Partia Paw\u0142a Piskorskiego zasili Koalicj\u0119 Europejsk\u0105? Jest wniosek o akces|website=dorzeczy.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref> [[Polish People's Party]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wiadomosci.gazeta.pl/wiadomosci/7,114884,24485461,psl-wchodzi-do-koalicji-europejskiej-kosiniak-kamysz-to-nie.html#s=BoxOpImg1|title=PSL wchodzi do Koalicji Europejskiej. Kosiniak-Kamysz: To nie jest \"antyzwi\u0105zek\"|website=gazeta.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-23}}</ref> [[Union of European Democrats]] (since 23 February), [[Social Democracy of Poland]] (since 2 March),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sdpl.pl/2019/03/02/konwent-krajowy-postanowil-socjaldemokracja-polska-przystepuje-do-koalicji-europejskiej/|title=Konwent krajowy postanowi\u0142: Socjaldemokracja Polska przyst\u0119puje do Koalicji Europejskiej|website=sdpl.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-03-02}}</ref> [[Union of the Left (Poland)|Liberty and Equality]] (since 3 March),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wir.info.pl/ke/|title=Rada Krajowa WiR w sprawie przyst\u0105pienia do Koalicji Europejskiej|last=Musia\u0142|first=Piotr|website=wir.info.pl|language=pl-PL|access-date=2019-03-04}}</ref> [[League of Polish Families]] (since 11 March)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wiadomosci.radiozet.pl/Polska/Liga-Polskich-Rodzin-popiera-Koalicje-Europejska.-Chce-sie-znalezc-na-jej-listach||title=Liga Polskich Rodzin popiera Koalicj\u0119 Europejsk\u0105. Chce si\u0119 znale\u017c\u0107 na jej listach|website=radiozet.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-03-11}}</ref> and [[Feminist Initiative (Poland)|Feminist Initiative]] (since 15 March).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rp.pl/Sojusz-Lewicy-Demokratycznej/190319501-Czarzasty-Nie-musimy-tak-samo-myslec-o-aborcji.html|title=Czarzasty: Nie musimy tak samo my\u015ble\u0107 o aborcji|website=www.rp.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-04-03}}</ref> \n\nThe Coalition also gained the support from [[Barbara Nowacka]] and her movement, the [[Poland Initiative]] and civic organisation [[Committee for the Defence of Democracy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pap.pl/aktualnosci/news,421962,kod-bedzie-wspieral-koalicje-europejska-przed-wyborami-do-pe.html|title=KOD b\u0119dzie wspiera\u0142 Koalicj\u0119 Europejsk\u0105 przed wyborami do PE {{!}} Polska Agencja Prasowa SA|website=www.pap.pl|access-date=2019-03-17}}</ref> \n\nThe Coalition came in second place in the [[2019 European Parliament election in Poland|2019 European Parliament election]] with 38.5% of the vote, returning 22 MEPs.<ref>https://www.euractiv.com/section/eu-elections-2019/news/polands-pis-wins-eu-polls-braces-for-decisive-battle-in-autumn/</ref>\n\nThe disappointing results led the agrarian [[Polish People's Party]] (PSL) to opt out of the coalition and set up the [[Polish Coalition]] instead, which should not include leftist parties.\n\n== Signatories ==\nProminent signatories of the European Coalition's foundation appeal include:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvn24.pl/r/905696|title=\"Koalicja europejska dla Polski\". Apel by\u0142ych premier\u00f3w i szef\u00f3w dyplomacji|website=TVN24.pl|access-date=2019-02-04}}</ref> \n* [[Marek Belka]] ([[Democratic Left Alliance|SLD]]), former prime minister (2004\u201305), former president of the National Bank of Poland (2010\u201316)\n* [[Jerzy Buzek]] ([[Civic Platform|PO]]), former prime minister (1997\u20132001), former president of the European Parliament (2009\u20132012)\n* [[W\u0142odzimierz Cimoszewicz]] (SLD), former prime minister (1996\u201397), former minister of foreign affairs (2001\u201305)\n* [[Ewa Kopacz]] (PO), former prime minister (2014\u201315), former marshal of the Sejm (2011\u201314)\n* [[Kazimierz Marcinkiewicz]] (ex-[[Law and Justice|PiS]]), former prime minister (2005\u201306)\n* [[Leszek Miller]] (SLD), former prime minister (2001\u201304)\n* [[Adam Daniel Rotfeld]], former minister of foreign affairs (2005)\n* [[Grzegorz Schetyna]] (PO), leader of PO (since 2016), former minister of foreign affairs (2014\u201315), former marshal of the Sejm (2010\u201311)\n* [[Rados\u0142aw Sikorski]] (PO), former minister of foreign affairs (2007\u201314), former marshal of the Sejm (2014\u201315)\n* [[Hanna Suchocka]] (ex-[[Democratic Union (Poland)|UD]]/[[Freedom Union (Poland)|UW]]), former prime minister (1992\u201393)\n\n== Composition ==\nThe main parties include the following:\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:200px\" colspan=\"2\"|Name\n!style=\"width:120px\"|Ideology\n!style=\"width:90px\"|Position\n!style=\"width:140px\"|Leader\n![[Sejm|MPs]]{{efn|As of 5 April 2019 (unchanged since 13 December 2018). A detailed table of parliamentary group swings in the Lower House can be found on the Polish Wikipedia [[:pl:Pos\u0142owie na Sejm Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej VIII kadencji#Zmiany liczebno\u015bci klub\u00f3w w czasie kadencji|article regarding the 8th Sejm]].}}\n![[Senate of Poland|Senators]]\n![[European Parliament|MEPs]]\n!Entry\n|-\n|style=\"width:2px;background:{{Civic Platform/meta/color}};\"|\n|[[Civic Platform]]\n|[[Liberal conservatism]]\n|[[Centre politics|Centre]] to [[centre-right politics|centre-right]]\n|[[Grzegorz Schetyna]]\n|{{composition bar|145|460|#FAA14C}}\n|{{composition bar|27|100|#FAA14C}}\n|{{composition bar|18|51|#FAA14C}}\n|data-sort-value=\"2019-02-21\"|21 February\n|-\n|style=\"width:2px;background:{{Modern (political party)/meta/color}};\"|\n|[[Modern (political party)|Modern]]\n|[[Liberalism]]\n|[[Centre politics|Centre]]\n|[[Katarzyna Lubnauer]]\n|{{composition bar|14|460|hex={{Modern (political party)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|0|100|}}\n|{{composition bar|0|51|}}\n|data-sort-value=\"2019-02-22\"|22 February\n|-\n|style=\"width:2px;background:{{Democratic Left Alliance/meta/color}};\"|\n|[[Democratic Left Alliance]]\n|[[Social democracy]]\n|[[Centre-left politics|Centre-left]]\n|[[:pl:W\u0142odzimierz Czarzasty|W\u0142odzimierz Czarzasty]]\n|{{composition bar|0|460|}}\n|{{composition bar|0|100|}}\n|{{composition bar|3|51|hex=Red}}\n|data-sort-value=\"2019-02-16\"|16 February\n|-\n|style=\"width:2px;background:{{Polish People's Party/meta/color}};\"|\n|[[Polish People's Party]]\n|[[Christian democracy]]\n|[[Centre-right politics|Centre-right]]\n|[[W\u0142adys\u0142aw Kosiniak-Kamysz]]\n|{{composition bar|14|460|hex={{Polish People's Party/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|1|100|hex={{Polish People's Party/meta/color}}}}\n|{{composition bar|4|51|hex={{Polish People's Party/meta/color}}}}\n|data-sort-value=\"2019-02-23\"|23 February\n|-\n|style=\"width:2px;background:#00C000;\"|\n|[[The Greens (Poland)|The Greens (Zieloni)]]\n|[[Green politics]]\n|[[Centre-left politics|Centre-left]]\n|[[:pl:Marek Kossakowski (dziennikarz)|Marek Kossakowski]]<br>[[Ma\u0142gorzata Tracz]]\n|{{composition bar|0|460|}}\n|{{composition bar|0|100|}}\n|{{composition bar|0|51|}}\n|data-sort-value=\"2019-02-17\"|17 February\n|}\n\nAlso affiliated to the coalition include the following:\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:200px\" colspan=\"2\"|Name\n!style=\"width:120px\"|Ideology\n!style=\"width:90px\"|Position\n!style=\"width:140px\"|Leader\n![[Sejm|MPs]]\n![[Senate of Poland|Senators]]\n![[European Parliament|MEPs]]\n!Entry\n|-\n|style=\"width:2px;background:{{Now! (political party)/meta/color}};\"|\n|[[Now! (political party)|Now!]]\n|[[Liberalism]]\n|[[Centre politics|Centre]]\n|[[Ryszard Petru]]\n|{{composition bar|3|460|hex=Darkblue}}\n|{{composition bar|0|100|}}\n|{{composition bar|0|51|}}\n|data-sort-value=\"2019-02-18\"|18 February\n|-\n|style=\"width:2px;background:#F0D719;\"|\n|[[Union of European Democrats]]\n|[[Social liberalism]]\n|[[Centre politics|Centre]]\n|[[:pl:El\u017cbieta Bi\u0144czycka|El\u017cbieta Bi\u0144czycka]]\n|{{composition bar|3|460|hex=#F0D719}}\n|{{composition bar|0|100|}}\n|{{composition bar|0|51|}}\n|data-sort-value=\"2019-02-23\"|23 February\n|-\n|style=\"width:2px;background:{{Democratic Party (Poland)/meta/color}};\"|\n|[[Alliance of Democrats (Poland)|Alliance of Democrats]]\n|[[Liberalism]]\n|[[Centre politics|Centre]]\n|[[Pawe\u0142 Piskorski]]\n|{{composition bar|0|460|}}\n|{{composition bar|0|100|}}\n|{{composition bar|0|51|}}\n|data-sort-value=\"2019-02-22\"|22 February\n|-\n|style=\"width:2px;background:{{Social Democracy of Poland/meta/color}};\"|\n|[[Social Democracy of Poland]]\n|[[Social democracy]]\n|[[Centre-left politics|Centre-left]]\n|Wojciech Filemonowicz\n|{{composition bar|0|460|}}\n|{{composition bar|1|100|hex=Red}}\n|{{composition bar|0|51|}}\n|data-sort-value=\"2019-03-02\"|2 March\n|-\n|style=\"width:2px;background:red;\"|\n|[[Union of the Left (Poland)|Liberty and Equality]]\n|[[Social democracy]]\n|[[Centre-left politics|Centre-left]]\n|Piotr Musia\u0142\n|{{composition bar|0|460|}}\n|{{composition bar|0|100|}}\n|{{composition bar|0|51|}}\n|data-sort-value=\"2019-03-03\"|3 March\n|-\n|style=\"width:2px;background:{{League of Polish Families/meta/color}};\"|\n|[[League of Polish Families]]\n|[[Christian democracy]]\n|[[Centre-right]]\n|Witold Ba\u0142a\u017cak\n|{{composition bar|0|460}}\n|{{composition bar|0|100|}}\n|{{composition bar|0|51|}}\n|data-sort-value=\"2019-03-11\"|11 March\n|-\n|style=\"width:2px;background:#0093AF;\"|\n|[[Feminist Initiative (Poland)|Feminist Initiative]]\n|[[Feminism]]\n|[[Centre-left politics|Centre-left]]\n|Collective {{small|(Katarzyna K\u0105dziela, El\u017cbieta Jachlewska, Iwona Pi\u0105tek)}}\n|{{composition bar|0|460}}\n|{{composition bar|0|100}}\n|{{composition bar|0|51}}\n|data-sort-value=\"2019-03-15\"|15 March\n|}\n\n== Candidates ==\nThe European Coalition lists in the 13 constituencies are headed by:<ref>https://wiadomosci.radiozet.pl/Eurowybory-2019/Kandydaci/Listy-kandydatow-do-Parlamentu-Europejskiego-Koalicja-Europejska-WYBORY-2019</ref>\n* District 1 ([[Pomeranian (European Parliament constituency)|Pomeranian]]): [[Janusz Lewandowski]] (PO)\n* District 2 ([[Kuyavian-Pomeranian (European Parliament constituency)|Kuyavian-Pomeranian]]): [[Rados\u0142aw Sikorski]] (PO)\n* District 3 ([[Podlaskie and Warmian-Masurian (European Parliament constituency)|Podlaskie and Warmian-Masurian]]): [[Tomasz Frankowski]] (PO)\n* District 4 ([[Warsaw (European Parliament constituency)|Warsaw]]): [[W\u0142odzimierz Cimoszewicz]] (SLD)\n* District 5 ([[Masovian (European Parliament constituency)|Masovian]], except Warsaw): [[Jaros\u0142aw Kalinowski]] (PSL)\n* District 6 ([[\u0141\u00f3d\u017a (European Parliament constituency)|\u0141\u00f3d\u017a]]): [[Marek Belka]] (SLD)\n* District 7 ([[Greater Poland (European Parliament constituency)|Greater Poland]]): [[Ewa Kopacz]] (PO)\n* District 8 ([[Lublin (European Parliament constituency)|Lublin]]): [[Krzysztof Hetman]] (PSL)\n* District 9 ([[Podkarpackie (European Parliament constituency)|Podkarpackie]]): [[Czes\u0142aw Siekierski]] (PSL)\n* District 10 ([[Lesser Poland and \u015awi\u0119tokrzyskie (European Parliament constituency)|Lesser Poland and \u015awi\u0119tokrzyskie]]): [[R\u00f3\u017ca Thun|R\u00f3\u017ca Gr\u00e4fin von Thun und Hohenstein]] (PO)\n* District 11 ([[Silesian (European Parliament constituency)|Silesian]]): [[Jerzy Buzek]] (PO)\n* District 12 ([[Lower Silesian and Opole (European Parliament constituency)|Lower Silesian and Opole]]): [[Janina Ochojska]] (non-partisan, [[Polish Humanitarian Action]])\n* District 13 ([[Lubusz and West Pomeranian (European Parliament constituency)|Lubusz and West Pomeranian]]): [[Bogus\u0142aw Liberadzki]] (SLD)\n\n== Results ==\n=== European Parliament ===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Year\n!Leader\n!Vote\n!Vote %\n!Seats\n!Place\n|-\n|[[2019 European Parliament election in Poland|2019]]\n|[[Grzegorz Schetyna]]{{efn|As the leader of the biggest party of the coalition.}}\n|5 249 935\n|38,47\n|{{composition bar|22|52|#0087BD}}\n|2\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Confederation KORWiN Braun Liroy Nationalists]]\n* [[United Right (Poland)|United Right]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n[[Category:2019 disestablishments in Poland]]\n[[Category:2019 establishments in Poland]]\n[[Category:Defunct political party alliances in Poland]]\n[[Category:Liberal parties in Poland]]\n[[Category:Political parties disestablished in 2019]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 2019]]\n<references group=\"nb\"/>\n", "text_old": "{{use dmy dates|date=July 2012}}\n{{short description|Liberal electoral alliance in Poland}}\n{{Infobox political party\n| name = European Coalition\n| logo = Logo-KE-podstawowe-biale-tlo.svg\n| colorcode = #0087BD\n| leader = {{\u2022}}[[Grzegorz Schetyna]]<br>{{\u2022}}[[W\u0142adys\u0142aw Kosiniak-Kamysz]]<br>{{\u2022}}[[:pl:W\u0142odzimierz Czarzasty|W\u0142odzimierz Czarzasty]]<br>{{\u2022}}[[Katarzyna Lubnauer]]<br>{{\u2022}}[[:pl:Marek Kossakowski (dziennikarz)|Marek Kossakowski]]<br>{{\u2022}}Ma\u0142gorzata Tracz\n| foundation = 1 February 2019\n| dissolved = 26 May 2019\n| ideology = [[Pro-Europeanism]]<br>[[Liberal democracy]]<br>[[Big tent]]\n| european = \n| headquarters = ul. Wiejska 12a, 00-490 [[Warsaw]], [[Poland]]\n| website = {{url|https://koalicjaeuropejska.pl}}\n| country = Poland\n| native_name = Koalicja Europejska\n| position = [[Big tent]]\n| seats1_title = [[Sejm of the Republic of Poland|Sejm]]\n| seats1 = {{composition bar|213|460|hex=#0087BD}}\n| seats2_title = [[Senate of Poland|Senate]]\n| seats2 = {{composition bar|48|100|hex=#0087BD}}\n| seats3_title = [[European Parliament]]\n| seats3 = {{composition bar|22|52|hex=#0087BD}}\n| abbreviation = KE\n| colors = {{color box|#0087BD|border=darkgray}} [[Blue]]\n}}\nThe '''European Coalition''' ({{lang-pl|Koalicja Europejska}}, KE) is a [[political alliance]] and [[electoral list]] in Poland established in 2019 by a group of former [[Prime Minister of Poland|prime ministers]] and former [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Poland)|foreign ministers]], including [[Jerzy Buzek]], [[Ewa Kopacz]], [[Grzegorz Schetyna]] and [[Rados\u0142aw Sikorski]]. They declared the will to construct \"one broad list in [[2019 European Parliament election|European Parliament election]], the aim of which would be to restore Poland's strong position in the [[European Union]]\". The Coalition is to be [[Pro-Europeanism|pro-European]] and [[Centrism|centrist]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wiadomosci.onet.pl/tylko-w-onecie/koniec-koalicji-obywatelskiej-schetyna-pokazuje-nowy-szyld/vx5e888|title=Koniec Koalicji Obywatelskiej, Schetyna pokazuje nowy szyld|date=2019-02-01|website=Onet Wiadomo\u015bci|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-04}}</ref>\n\nParties included in the coalition are the [[Democratic Left Alliance]] (since 16 February),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wiadomosci.gazeta.pl/wiadomosci/7,114884,24463976,sld-dolacza-do-koalicji-europejskiej-na-eurowybory-kandydatami.html|title=SLD do\u0142\u0105cza do Koalicji Europejskiej na eurowybory. Kandydatami m.in. Miller, Belka i Cimoszewicz|website=gazetapl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-17}}</ref> [[The Greens (Poland)|The Greens]] (since 17 February),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fakty.interia.pl/raporty/raport-ue-przed-wyborami-europejskimi/artykuly/news-zieloni-postanowili-o-dolaczeniu-do-koalicji-europejskiej,nId,2840963|title=Koalicja Europejska ro\u015bnie w si\u0142\u0119. Przyst\u0105pi\u0142a kolejna partia|website=fakty.interia.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-17}}</ref> [[Now! (political party)|Now!]] (since 18 February),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wyborcza.pl/7,75398,24469339,partia-teraz-dolacza-do-koalicji-europejskiej.html|title=Partia Teraz! do\u0142\u0105cza do Koalicji Europejskiej|website=wyborcza.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-18}}</ref> [[Civic Platform]] (since 21 February),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fakty.interia.pl/raporty/raport-ue-przed-wyborami-europejskimi/artykuly/news-zarzad-po-poparl-sfinalizowanie-koalicji-europejskiej,nId,2847871|title=Zarz\u0105d PO zadecydowa\u0142 w sprawie koalicji|website=fakty.interia.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref> [[.Modern|Modern]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://natemat.pl/264793,niedoficjalnie-nowoczesna-wchodzi-do-koalicji-europejskiej|title=Koalicja Europejska coraz wi\u0119ksza. Kolejna partia na wsp\u00f3lnych listach opozycji do europarlamentu|website=naTemat.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref> [[Alliance of Democrats (Poland)|Democratic Party]] (since 22 February),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dorzeczy.pl/kraj/94434/Partia-Pawla-Piskorskiego-zasili-Koalicje-Europejska-Jest-wniosek-o-akces.html|title=Partia Paw\u0142a Piskorskiego zasili Koalicj\u0119 Europejsk\u0105? Jest wniosek o akces|website=dorzeczy.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-22}}</ref> [[Polish People's Party]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wiadomosci.gazeta.pl/wiadomosci/7,114884,24485461,psl-wchodzi-do-koalicji-europejskiej-kosiniak-kamysz-to-nie.html#s=BoxOpImg1|title=PSL wchodzi do Koalicji Europejskiej. Kosiniak-Kamysz: To nie jest \"antyzwi\u0105zek\"|website=gazeta.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-02-23}}</ref> [[Union of European Democrats]] (since 23 February), [[Social Democracy of Poland]] (since 2 March),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sdpl.pl/2019/03/02/konwent-krajowy-postanowil-socjaldemokracja-polska-przystepuje-do-koalicji-europejskiej/|title=Konwent krajowy postanowi\u0142: Socjaldemokracja Polska przyst\u0119puje do Koalicji Europejskiej|website=sdpl.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-03-02}}</ref> [[Union of the Left (Poland)|Liberty and Equality]] (since 3 March),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wir.info.pl/ke/|title=Rada Krajowa WiR w sprawie przyst\u0105pienia do Koalicji Europejskiej|last=Musia\u0142|first=Piotr|website=wir.info.pl|language=pl-PL|access-date=2019-03-04}}</ref> [[League of Polish Families]] (since 11 March)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wiadomosci.radiozet.pl/Polska/Liga-Polskich-Rodzin-popiera-Koalicje-Europejska.-Chce-sie-znalezc-na-jej-listach||title=Liga Polskich Rodzin popiera Koalicj\u0119 Europejsk\u0105. Chce si\u0119 znale\u017c\u0107 na jej listach|website=radiozet.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-03-11}}</ref> and [[Feminist Initiative (Poland)|Feminist Initiative]] (since 15 March).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rp.pl/Sojusz-Lewicy-Demokratycznej/190319501-Czarzasty-Nie-musimy-tak-samo-myslec-o-aborcji.html|title=Czarzasty: Nie musimy tak samo my\u015ble\u0107 o aborcji|website=www.rp.pl|language=pl|access-date=2019-04-03}}</ref> \n\nThe Coalition also gained the support from [[Barbara Nowacka]] and her movement, the [[Poland Initiative]] and civic organisation [[Committee for the Defence of Democracy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pap.pl/aktualnosci/news,421962,kod-bedzie-wspieral-koalicje-europejska-przed-wyborami-do-pe.html|title=KOD b\u0119dzie wspiera\u0142 Koalicj\u0119 Europejsk\u0105 przed wyborami do PE {{!}} Polska Agencja Prasowa SA|website=www.pap.pl|access-date=2019-03-17}}</ref> \n\nThe Coalition came in second place in the [[2019 European Parliament election in Poland|2019 European Parliament election]] with 38.5% of the vote, returning 22 MEPs.<ref>https://www.euractiv.com/section/eu-elections-2019/news/polands-pis-wins-eu-polls-braces-for-decisive-battle-in-autumn/</ref>\n\nThe disappointing results led the agrarian [[Polish People's Party]] (PSL) to opt out of the coalition and set up the [[Polish Coalition]] instead, which should not include leftist parties.\n\n== Signatories ==\nProminent signatories of the European Coalition's foundation appeal include:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvn24.pl/r/905696|title=\"Koalicja europejska dla Polski\". Apel by\u0142ych premier\u00f3w i szef\u00f3w dyplomacji|website=TVN24.pl|access-date=2019-02-04}}</ref> \n* [[Marek Belka]] ([[Democratic Left Alliance|SLD]]), former prime minister (2004\u201305), former president of the National Bank of Poland (2010\u201316)\n* [[Jerzy Buzek]] ([[Civic Platform|PO]]), former prime minister (1997\u20132001), former president of the European Parliament (2009\u20132012)\n* [[W\u0142odzimierz Cimoszewicz]] (SLD), former prime minister (1996\u201397), former minister of foreign affairs (2001\u201305)\n* [[Ewa Kopacz]] (PO), former prime minister (2014\u201315), former marshal of the Sejm (2011\u201314)\n* [[Kazimierz Marcinkiewicz]] (ex-[[Law and Justice|PiS]]), former prime minister (2005\u201306)\n* [[Leszek Miller]] (SLD), former prime minister (2001\u201304)\n* [[Adam Daniel Rotfeld]], former minister of foreign affairs (2005)\n* [[Grzegorz Schetyna]] (PO), leader of PO (since 2016), former minister of foreign affairs (2014\u201315), former marshal of the Sejm (2010\u201311)\n* [[Rados\u0142aw Sikorski]] (PO), former minister of foreign affairs (2007\u201314), former marshal of the Sejm (2014\u201315)\n* [[Hanna Suchocka]] (ex-[[Democratic Union (Poland)|UD]]/[[Freedom Union (Poland)|UW]]), former prime minister (1992\u201393)\n\n== Composition ==\nThe main parties include the following:\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n!style=\"width:200px\" colspan=\"2\"|Name\n!style=\"width:120px\"|Ideology\n!style=\"width:90px\"|Position\n!style=\"width:140px\"|Leader\n![[Sejm|MPs]]{{efn|As of 5 April 2019 (unchanged since 13 December 2018). A detailed table of parliamentary group swings in the Lower House can be found on the Polish Wikipedia [[:pl:Pos\u0142owie na Sejm Rzeczypospolitej Polskiej VIII kadencji#Zmiany liczebno\u015bci klub\u00f3w w czasie kadencji|article regarding the 8th Sejm]].}}\n![[Senate of Poland|Senators]]\n![[European Parliament|MEPs]]\n!Entry\n|-\n|style=\"width:2px;background:{{Civic Platform/meta/color}};\"|\n|[[Civic Platform]]\n|[[Liberal conservatism]]\n|[[Centre politics|Centre]] to [[centre-right politics|centre-right]]\n|[[Grzegorz Schetyna]]\n|{{composition bar|145|460|#FAA14C}}\n|{{composition bar|27|100|#FAA14C}}\n|{{composition bar|18|51|#FA